message: "If you use this repository, please cite the software artifact below."
title: "Religious Text Anchors and Moral Attention Reallocation in Language Models"
type: software
version: "v0.1-confirmation"
date-released: 2026-04-12
license: Apache-2.0
authors:
  - family-names: Zhu
    given-names: Hanzhen
    email: jennyzhu@g.harvard.edu
repository-code: "https://github.com/hanzhenzhujene/moral-attention-reallocation"
url: "https://github.com/hanzhenzhujene/moral-attention-reallocation"
abstract: >-
  A pre-freeze research artifact for studying whether generic heart-focused
  framing and cross-tradition religious text anchors reallocate moral
  attention in language models toward inward motive and disposition rather
  than outward behavioral surface. The cross-tradition anchors are
  implemented as frozen study paraphrases keyed to cited Biblical,
  Buddhist, Hindu, and Islamic passages. The repository now exposes two
  linked artifact layers: a project-level six-condition cross-tradition
  readout on the confirmation slice, and a narrower frozen release artifact
  centered on the baseline-versus-heart-focused comparison.
keywords:
  - llm evaluation
  - moral reasoning
  - moral psychology
  - benchmark design
  - framing effects
